# Public base URL where this mirror is served (the web root is ./public).
# It is used verbatim to build packages.json "providers-url", so it MUST end
# with a trailing slash. Copy this file to .env and adjust.
#
# GitHub Pages project site (the default below): the site is served at
#   https://<user>.github.io/<repo>/
# so a root-relative path that is just the repo name works, e.g.
#   "/asset-packagist-mirror/" -> "/asset-packagist-mirror/p/...".
# This avoids hard-coding the domain, so it stays portable across forks and
# custom domains (only the path segment matters).
#
# Custom domain example: this repo's Pages site (imzyf.github.io) is mapped to
# zyf.im, so the mirror lives at https://zyf.im/asset-packagist-mirror/. The
# domain changed but the "/asset-packagist-mirror/" path did not, so RAW_BASE
# stays the same -- that is exactly why the root-relative path is portable.
#
# Other options:
# - Self-hosted nginx with the web root at "/": leave it as "/" (root-relative).
# - Absolute URL (note the trailing slash), e.g. a custom domain or GitHub raw:
#     RAW_BASE=https://composer.example.com/
#     RAW_BASE=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/imzyf/asset-packagist-mirror/main/public/

RAW_BASE=/asset-packagist-mirror/
